Founders' week is ever to be kept in the memory of the students of Old Union by holding all the social and literary events of the winter term at that time. This year Charter day falls on Thursday, February 18. The Allison--Foote prize debate will be held on the evening of Charter day in the First Presbyterian Church. The subject for debate is, \A wise policy for the United States precludes territorial acquisition.\ The two literary societies will contest for the prize of $5o which will be awarded to the society presenting as a whole the stronge&t argument.
